<TITLE> July 4 set for verdict in Mir Nasir case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 25 (bdnews24.com) A verdict will be delivered in the corruption case against former state minister and BNP leader Mir Nasiruddin and son Mir Md Helaluddin on July 4. Anticorruption Commission (ACC) deputy director Sharmeen Ferdousi filed the case with Gulshan Police Station on March 6. Nasir and Helal are accused of acquiring assets beyond their known sources of income. A chargesheet, submitted on April 29, stated that the accused supplied false wealth statements to the ACC. The ACC alleged that the existence of Tk 3.22 crore in assets was suppressed in the wealth statement. Judge Amar Kumar Roy of the Special Judge's Court heard testimonies from 32 witnesses. bdnews24
